# Equivalents for tiers.py — see equivalents-security-core.md (Category T1).
# Each entry is a mutant proven GENUINELY EQUIVALENT: no honest input
# distinguishes it from the original for ANY reachable input. Excluded from the
# kill-rate denominator. Killable siblings are killed by tests in
# tests/hooks/modules/security/test_tiers_mutants.py and test_tiers.py.
#
# IDENTITY FORMAT (re-init-proof): each entry is the mutant's STABLE identity
#   operator_name|start_row:start_col-end_row:end_col|occurrence
# NOT a job_id (cosmic-ray regenerates job_ids on every `init`; a job_id-keyed
# skip silently matches nothing after re-init -- the false-100% trap). The
# harness (mutkill_approval_grants.py: stable_id / compute_skip_jobids) resolves
# these to the current session and WARNS on any unmatched token.
#
# Re-keyed against tiers.sqlite (87 specs, dedicated per-module session at
# post-desacople HEAD). The earlier baseline used tiers-spike.sqlite (a
# different session); this is the COMPLETE module measured on its own toml.
# 28 survivors: 1 killable (L96 GtE_Eq) is now killed by
# test_tiers_mutants.py::TestTiersFastPathAndDryRun; the 27 below are equivalent.
#
# ===========================================================================
# T1a — requires_approval `return self == SecurityTier.T3_BLOCKED` (L40).
# Domain of self is the 4 enum singletons. Eq_Is: enum members are singletons
# so `is` coincides with `==`. Eq_GtE: SecurityTier is (str, Enum) "T0".."T3";
# "T3" is the max, so `self >= T3` is True iff `self == T3` -- identical truth
# table over all 4 members.
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_GtE|40:20-40:22|0
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_Is|40:20-40:22|0
# ===========================================================================
# T1b — @lru_cache(maxsize=512) on _classify_command_tier_cached (L79). The
# function is pure over (command, has_blocked_patterns). RemoveDecorator only
# forgoes caching; the maxsize NumberReplacers change only eviction capacity.
# Neither changes any return value.
core/RemoveDecorator|79:0-80:0|2
core/NumberReplacer|79:19-79:22|0
core/NumberReplacer|79:19-79:22|1
# ===========================================================================
# T1c — ultra-common fast-path guards (L100/L101). The fast-path is a PURE
# OPTIMIZATION: every ULTRA_COMMON_T0 command also classifies T0 via the slow
# path (none is mutative, none hits a T1/T2 keyword), so the safe-by-elimination
# default at L138 returns the SAME T0. Altering the L100 length guard or the
# L101 index therefore cannot change any observable.
#   NOTE: the L96 `>= 2` GtE_Eq is NOT here -- it IS killable ('git diff HEAD'
#   is T0 via prefix2 but T2 via the 'diff' keyword on the slow path) and is
#   killed by a test. Only the L100/L101 guards (slow path also T0) are equiv.
core/AddNot|100:7-100:22|3
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_GtE_Eq|100:18-100:20|1
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_GtE_Gt|100:18-100:20|1
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_GtE_Lt|100:18-100:20|1
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_GtE_LtE|100:18-100:20|1
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_GtE_NotEq|100:18-100:20|1
core/NumberReplacer|100:21-100:22|8
core/NumberReplacer|100:21-100:22|9
core/NumberReplacer|101:17-101:18|11
# ===========================================================================
# T1d — dry-run gate `"--dry-run" in command or "--plan-only" in command`
# (L109) ReplaceOrWithAnd. LOOKS killable but is equivalent: with `and` the
# gate needs both flags, yet every command that reached it is rescued
# downstream -- a `--dry-run` command has verb-detector category SIMULATION and
# returns T2 at L132; a `--plan-only` command contains the word "plan" and
# matches the \bplan\b T2 regex at L113. So the observable T2 is unchanged for
# all reachable inputs.
core/ReplaceOrWithAnd|109:30-109:32|1
# T1d2 — public empty-guard `not command or not command.strip()` (L178)
# ReplaceOrWithAnd. Diverges from `or` only for whitespace-only input; with
# `and` it short-circuits False, strips to "", the blocked-pattern loop matches
# nothing, and _classify_command_tier_cached("") hits its OWN (unmutated) L89
# guard and returns T3 -- identical observable. The cached guard masks it.
core/ReplaceOrWithAnd|178:19-178:21|2
# ===========================================================================
# T1e — `*,` keyword-only marker in classify_command_tier signature (L143).
# ReplaceBinaryOperator_Mul_Div targets a `*` token, but here `*` is the bare
# keyword-only separator, not a binary operation; the mutation leaves the
# signature semantics unchanged (no operand to divide), so no input observes it.
core/ReplaceBinaryOperator_Mul_Div|143:4-143:5|0
# ===========================================================================
# T1f — verb-detector result branches (L132 SIMULATION, L134 READ_ONLY).
# CATEGORY_* are module constants; result.category is the SAME object the dict
# returns, so `==`->`is` (Eq_Is) coincides by identity. For L134, a READ_ONLY
# command returns T0 and the L138 default ALSO returns T0, so every `==` flip
# (NotEq/Gt/GtE/Lt/LtE/IsNot) and AddNot leaves the observable T0 unchanged.
# L132 SIMULATION is unreachable with a SIMULATION category that is not already
# caught by the T2 keyword scan at L113 (plan/diff/template), so its Eq_Is flip
# is unobservable too.
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_Is|132:23-132:25|1
core/AddNot|134:7-134:44|11
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_Gt|134:23-134:25|2
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_GtE|134:23-134:25|2
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_Is|134:23-134:25|2
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_IsNot|134:23-134:25|2
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_Lt|134:23-134:25|2
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_LtE|134:23-134:25|2
core/ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_NotEq|134:23-134:25|2
